<br>
So, there I was, kiting wyverns in CS, had dinged 49 the night before and had built up a decent buffer. I get a tell from a guy asking if I want to join a Naggy raid. I thought about it, and said what the hell. I'm not in a raiding guild, and have never been on a raid.<br>
<br>
I port over to Nektulos and run to the druid ring in Lavastorm where they're meeting to assign groups and such. We get our groups assigned, gather the few remaining necessities (it was a pickup raid) and head in.<br>
<br>
Most of the giants had already been cleared, so we slaughtered a few kobolds, bats, and LDC's on the way in. We get to the &quot;prep&quot; room, and pull a couple of FG warriors and Magus Rokyll. Fight went really simply. I had a couple of resists on Rokyll, but my group still managed to do enough damage to him and the FG's to get xp. (Most of the people there were Non-PoP so we weren't using the raid system.) We lost one ranger on that fight, so we rezzed him and then prepared for Naggy. <br>
<br>
Due to some miscommunication problems and only having one Shaman, the buffing process was rather slow and tedious. By the time they finished junk buffing everyone, some peoples junk buffs were wearing off so they had to redo them. Then the raid leader went LD on us. So by the time he came back, most of the junk buffs were wearing off so we had to repeat that whole process.<br>
<br>
So finally, we charge Naggy. We basically had a three group charge. The first group went in and the proverbial shit hit the proverbial fan. I still don't know what happened, but someone failed to heal the MA. He died in about the first six seconds of the fight. The raid leader said for everyone to charge, so in we went. The last two groups charged in and all the meatshields and such engaged Naggy. MOST of the caster group stayed outside the door to avoid debuffs and the AoE, but a couple ran inside so we lost them quickly too. When Naggy dropped to about 55%, we went in and started nuking. I had basically 8 junk buffs. I resisted the first AE, and he stripped my first four buffs. My first ice comet landed for full damage, yay me! Then he stripped my second four buffs, and he resisted my second IC. I thought it would be a good idea to recast some buffs, so I backed into the hallway, buffed up, and stepped back in and cast Ice Comet. But, I forgot to change targets. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   So, I Ice Cometed myself for 980 damage and took a trip to bind.<br>
<br>
We failed to take Naggy down, but it was fun as hell for me. Even with the embarrasing accidental suicide (which I told nobody in the raid about <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) The CR took three hours because two monks and one rogue left, leaving us one rogue and one monk to do all the corpse dragging. The poor monk died about eight more times during the CR process. But, we got everyone rezzed and I TL'ed people out that wanted to leave, etc. Due to the long CR, we didn't try him again, but I look forward to getting my revenge.<br>
<br>
Just wanted to share. It really re-interested me in the game. Quadding was getting really booring, but now I have something to look forward to. I can't wait to get in on some of the cooler raids. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
